# ${project.name}

A command-line tool for working with [OSCAL](https://pages.nist.gov/OSCAL/) (Open Security Controls Assessment Language) and [Metaschema](https://pages.nist.gov/metaschema/) content.

## Quick Start

### Using Docker

```bash
# Validate an OSCAL document
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd):/data" ghcr.io/metaschema-framework/oscal-cli:latest \
    validate /data/ssp.json

# Convert XML to JSON
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd):/data" ghcr.io/metaschema-framework/oscal-cli:latest \
    convert --to=json /data/catalog.xml /data/catalog.json
```

### Using the CLI Directly

```bash
# Validate an OSCAL document
oscal-cli validate ssp.json

# Convert between formats
oscal-cli convert --to=json catalog.xml catalog.json

# Resolve a profile
oscal-cli resolve-profile profile.json resolved-catalog.json
```

See the [Installation](installation.html) guide for download and setup instructions.

## Key Features

- **Validation** - Validate OSCAL documents for well-formedness and schema compliance
- **Format Conversion** - Convert between XML, JSON, and YAML formats
- **Profile Resolution** - Resolve OSCAL profiles to produce baseline catalogs
- **Metapath Queries** - Query OSCAL content using Metapath expressions
- **Schema Generation** - Generate XML and JSON schemas from Metaschema modules

## Common Commands

